Description: CVE-2026-4873 - Prevent reuse of non-TLS STARTTLS connections
 A connection requiring TLS incorrectly reuses an existing unencrypted
 connection from the same pool. If an initial transfer is made in
 clear-text (via IMAP, SMTP, or POP3), a subsequent request to that same
 host bypasses the TLS requirement and instead transmits data unencrypted.
 This patch adds a check in ConnectionExists() to reject reuse of a
 connection that has not been TLS-upgraded when the new request requires
 TLS (use_ssl >= CURLUSESSL_CONTROL).
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/curl/curl/commit/507e7be573b0a76fca597b75ff7cb27a66e7d865
