Description: CVE-2025-14017 - ldap: call ldap_init() before setting the options
 When doing multi-threaded LDAPS transfers with libcurl, ldap_set_option()
 was called with NULL as the LDAP handle for several TLS-related options,
 which sets them globally. This means changing TLS options in one thread
 could inadvertently affect other concurrent transfers. For example,
 disabling certificate verification for one transfer could unintentionally
 disable it for other threads.
 .
 Fix by calling ldap_init() (or ldap_sslinit() on Win32) before any
