Description: Fix CVE-2026-8932 incomplete mTLS config in connection reuse and session cache
 libcurl reused pooled connections and TLS sessions across easy handles when
 the client credential settings differed only on SSLKEY, SSLKEYTYPE,
 KEYPASSWD, SSLCERTTYPE or SSLKEYBLOB, because those five fields lived on
 ssl_config_data rather than ssl_primary_config and were therefore invisible
 to Curl_ssl_config_matches() and to the TLS session cache lookup. The
 second handle would silently inherit the first handle's authenticated
 identity.
 .
 Promote cert_type, key, key_type, key_passwd and key_blob from
 ssl_config_data into ssl_primary_config so that Curl_ssl_config_matches(),
 Curl_clone_primary_ssl_config() and Curl_free_primary_ssl_config() cover
 the complete client credential set, and retarget every TLS/SSH/LDAP/QUIC
 backend consumer accordingly.
