Description: CVE-2026-3784 - Fix proxy_info_matches() to compare proxy credentials
 curl would wrongly reuse an existing HTTP proxy connection doing CONNECT to
 a server, even if the new request uses different credentials for the HTTP
 proxy. The root cause is proxy_info_matches() omitting a credential
 comparison. This patch adds user/password comparison to proxy_info_matches()
 and eliminates the now-redundant socks_proxy_info_matches() function.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/curl/curl/commit/5f13a7645e565c5c1a06f3ef86e97afb856fb364
Author: Stefan Eissing <stefan@eissing.org>
Last-Update: 2026-03-13

