+
+# Why CVE-2025-10966 in `curl` / `libcurl` Is a False Positive on Debian Bookworm
+
+## Overview: What Is This CVE?
+
+**CVE-2025-10966** is a vulnerability in **libcurl** when SFTP is done using the **wolfSSH**-powered SSH backend. The code for managing SSH connections in that backend missed host verification mechanisms, which can prevent curl from detecting MITM attackers.
+
+Security scanners (e.g., Trivy, Grype, Snyk) may report this CVE when they see **curl** or **libcurl** in Debian Bookworm. This document explains in detail why **Debian Bookworm's curl/libcurl is not actually vulnerable** and why the finding should be treated as a **false positive**.
+
+---
+
+## CVE-2025-10966 – Technical Breakdown
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|--------|
+| **CVE** | CVE-2025-10966 |
+| **Title** | Missing SFTP host verification with wolfSSH |
+| **Component** | curl / libcurl (SFTP via **wolfSSH** backend only) |
+| **CWE** | CWE-322: Key Exchange without Entity Authentication |
+| **Upstream severity** | Low |
+| **Introduced in** | curl **7.69.0** |
+| **Fixed in** | curl **8.17.0** (released 2025-11-05); wolfSSH support removed |
+
+### Conditions Required for the Vulnerability to Apply
+
+The issue **only** applies when **all** of the following are true:
+
+1. **curl is built with wolfSSH** as the SSH backend (not libssh2 or libssh).
+2. The user performs **SFTP** transfers (the wolfSSH backend only supports SFTP, not SCP).
+3. curl version is in the affected range **7.69.0 through 8.16.0**.
+
+curl selects **one** SSH backend at **build-time**. If the build uses libssh2 or libssh instead of wolfSSH, the vulnerable code path is never used.
+
+If any of these conditions is false, the vulnerability **cannot be triggered**.
+
+---
+
+## Why Debian Bookworm Is Not Vulnerable
+
+### 1. Build Configuration: Debian Does Not Use wolfSSH
+
+The vulnerability **only** applies when curl is built with the **wolfSSH** SSH backend. Debian's curl package is built with **libssh2** (on Debian) or **libssh** (on Ubuntu), and **never** with wolfSSH.
+
+#### Evidence from Debian package source (curl 7.88.1-10+deb12u14, Bookworm)
+
+In **`debian/rules`**, the SSH backend is set explicitly:
+
+```makefile
+# disable libssh2 on Ubuntu (see #888449)
+ifeq ($(shell dpkg-vendor --derives-from Ubuntu && echo yes),yes)
+	CONFIGURE_ARGS += --with-libssh --without-libssh2
+else
+	CONFIGURE_ARGS += --without-libssh --with-libssh2
+endif
+```
+
+So on **Debian** (including Bookworm): `--without-libssh --with-libssh2` → SSH backend is **libssh2 only**. There is **no** `--with-wolfssh` anywhere in the rules.
+
+In **`debian/control`**, Build-Depends include `libssh-dev` and `libssh2-1-dev`. There is **no** build dependency on any wolfSSH package (e.g. `libwolfssh-dev`).
+
+| Source | URL |
+|--------|-----|
+| debian/rules | [sources.debian.org/src/curl/7.88.1-10+deb12u14/debian/rules](https://sources.debian.org/src/curl/7.88.1-10+deb12u14/debian/rules/) |
+| debian/control | [sources.debian.org/src/curl/7.88.1-10+deb12u14/debian/control](https://sources.debian.org/src/curl/7.88.1-10+deb12u14/debian/control/) |
+
+The **Debian Security Tracker** also states for CVE-2025-10966:
+
+> **Notes:** … **wolfSSH backend not used in Debian**
+
+So the condition for the vulnerability (curl built with wolfSSH) is **not met** on Debian. The vulnerable code path is **not used** in Debian's build.
+
+---
+
+### 2. Version (for completeness)
+
+**Debian Bookworm** ships **curl 7.88.1** (source package version `7.88.1-10+deb12u14`). The upstream affected range is **7.69.0 through 8.16.0**, so Bookworm's version is in that range. The reason Bookworm is not vulnerable is **not** the version but the **build configuration**: without wolfSSH, the flaw cannot be triggered.
+
+---
+
+## Summary Table: Debian Bookworm vs CVE-2025-10966
+
+| Check | Result |
+|-------|--------|
+| **Debian Bookworm curl version** | 7.88.1 |
+| **Affected version range (upstream)** | 7.69.0 – 8.16.0 (when built with wolfSSH) |
+| **Is Bookworm curl built with wolfSSH?** | **No** (`debian/rules`: `--with-libssh2` on Debian; no `--with-wolfssh`) |
+| **SSH backend in Debian Bookworm** | **libssh2** |
+| **Can this CVE be triggered on Bookworm?** | **No** |
+| **Conclusion** | **False positive** – no patch required for this CVE on Debian Bookworm |
+
+---
+
+## Recommendation for Scanners and Audits
+
+- **Treat CVE-2025-10966 as a false positive** for **Debian Bookworm**'s curl and libcurl packages.
+- **No code or package update is required** for this CVE on Bookworm; the vulnerable wolfSSH backend is not used.
+- If your policy or scanner cannot mark it as a false positive, this document and the Debian package source (`debian/rules`, `debian/control`) can be used as **evidence**.
